text: Sabina Tashkenbaeva (born 27 November 2000 in Tashkent, Uzbekistan) is an Uzbekistani rhythmic gymnast. Tashkenbaeva competed at the 2017 Islamic Solidarity Games, earning silver in the team event alongside compatriots Anastasiya Serdyukova and Nurinisso Usmanova, as well as bronze in both the clubs and ribbon individual competitionhttps://vestnikkavkaza.net/news/Sabina- Tashkenbaeva-I-leave-Islamic-games-in-Baku-in-a-wonderful-mood.html. She won the silver medal in both the individual all-around and team events at the 2018 Asian Games held in Jakarta, Indonesia.
